'''Alexander Nübel''' ({{IPA|de|alɛˈksandɐ ˈnyːbl̩}}; born 30 September 1996) is a German professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]] for {{German football updater|Stuttgart}} club [[VfB Stuttgart]], on loan from [[FC Bayern Munich|Bayern Munich]], and the [[Germany national football team|Germany national team]].<ref name="soccerway">{{Soccerway|alexander-nubel/348361}}</ref>

==Club career==
===Early years===
Nübel grew up in [[Salzkotten]]-Tudorf in [[North Rhine-Westphalia|East Westphalia]],<ref name="paderborner">{{cite news |last=Klute |first=Peter |title=Der gebürtige Paderborner Nübel spielt mit Schalke beim SCP: Riesenfreude auf die Rückkehr |url=https://www.westfalen-blatt.de/SCP/3954182-Der-gebuertige-Paderborner-Nuebel-spielt-mit-Schalke-beim-SCP-Riesenfreude-auf-die-Rueckkehr |access-date=11 February 2021 |newspaper=Westfalen-Blatt |date=11 September 2019 |language=de}}</ref> and began playing football at TSV Tudorf. In 2005 he moved to the youth department of [[SC Paderborn 07|SC Paderborn]], where he was initially active as an outfield player until under-14 level.<ref>{{Cite magazine|last=Schröter-Lorenz |first=Carsten |title=Nübel über die Schalke-Krise, Tedesco und die U 21|magazine=[[Kicker (magazine)|Kicker]]|issue=94 |date=2018 |page=31 |language=de}}</ref> Initially with Paderborn, he moved up to the professional squad for the 2014–15 season, but remained inactive throughout the season.

===Schalke 04===
[[File:Alexander Nübel.jpg|thumb|upright|Nübel with [[Schalke 04]] in 2016]]
Nübel moved to [[Schalke 04]] as its back-up goalkeeper to [[Ralf Fährmann]]. On 24 October 2018, he made his [[UEFA Champions League|Champions League]] debut for Schalke in a goalless draw against [[Galatasaray S.K. (football)|Galatasaray]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://de.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/match/2025100--galatasaray-vs-schalke/ |title=Galatasaray 0–0 Schalke |website=UEFA |date=24 October 2018 }}</ref>

After the winter break, Schalke's head coach [[Domenico Tedesco]], dropped Fährmann as the club's first-choice goalkeeper and promoted Nübel.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/alexander-nubel-bayern-goalkeeper-following-manuel-neuer-1765|title=Alexander Nübel: Who is the Schalke goalkeeper following in the footsteps of Manuel Neuer?|website=Bundesliga|date=1 June 2024|access-date=26 July 2025}}</ref> On 2 February 2019, Nübel was sent off with a straight red card in a match against [[Borussia Mönchengladbach]] and was suspended for the club's next two Bundesliga matches.<ref>{{cite web | url = https://www.worldfootball.net/match-report/ma8765767/lineup/ | title = Schalke vs Gladbach - Match report|website=WorldFootball|publisher=Heim: Spiel|access-date=25 August 2019}}</ref> Nübel started in every match for Schalke after he was selected as the first-choice goalkeeper, except two matches he was suspended for.

On 6 August 2019, Nübel was selected by Schalke's head coach [[David Wagner (soccer)|David Wagner]] as the club's new captain.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://schalke04.de/en/team/alexander-nuebel-named-new-royal-blues-captain/|title=Alexander Nübel named new Royal Blues captain |publisher=FC Schalke 04|accessdate=25 August 2019}}</ref> He entered the season with only one year left on his contract with Schalke. On 22 December 2019, Schalke revealed that Nübel had informed the club that he would not renew his contract.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://schalke04.de/en/team/alex-nuebel-leave-schalke-04-end-season/|title=Alex Nübel to leave Schalke 04 at the end of the season|website=FC Schalke 04|accessdate=22 December 2019}}</ref> On 4 January 2020, Nübel agreed to join [[FC Bayern Munich|Bayern Munich]] on a free transfer at the end of the season.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/50992409|title=Alexander Nubel: Schalke keeper to join Bayern Munich in summer|website=[[BBC Sport]]|publisher=[[BBC]]|date=4 January 2020}}</ref> He then handed the captaincy over to [[Omar Mascarell]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://schalke04.de/en/team/omar-mascarell-named-new-fc-schalke-04-captain/|title=Omar Mascarell named new FC Schalke 04 captain|website=FC Schalke 04|date=4 January 2020}}</ref>

===Bayern Munich===
Nübel joined [[Bayern Munich]] on 30 June 2020.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://fcbayern.com/en/news/2020/06/nuebel-passes-bayern-medical|title=Alexander Nübel completes medical at FC Bayern|website=FC Bayern Munich|date=30 June 2020}}</ref> He made his debut for Bayern in the first round of the [[2020–21 DFB-Pokal|DFB-Pokal]] on 15 October where the club defeated fifth division club [[1. FC Düren]] 3–0.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.dfb.de/dfb-pokal/spieltag/?spieledb_path=%2Fmatches%2F2311419|title=1. FC Düren 0:3 Bayern München|publisher=[[German Football Association]]|date=15 October 2020|language=de}}</ref> On 1 December 2020, he made his Champions League debut with Bayern in a 1–1 away draw against [[Atlético Madrid]] during the group stage of the [[2020–21 UEFA Champions League|2020–21 season]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://fcbayern.com/en/news/2020/12/reaction-bayern-draw-away-in-madrid-on-matchday-5-of-the-ucl |title=Reaction: Atlético Madrid vs. FC Bayern |website=FC Bayern Munich |date=2 December 2020 }}</ref> On 15 May 2021, he made his Bundesliga debut in a 2–2 away draw against [[SC Freiburg|Freiburg]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.sport1.de/fussball/bundesliga/2021/05/fc-bayern-alexander-nuebel-will-transfer-trotz-bundesliga-debuet |title= Nübel wird gelobt, will aber weg! |website=Sport1|language= de | date = 15 May 2021 | access-date = 16 May 2021}}</ref>

====2021–23: Loan to Monaco====
On 27 June 2021, Nübel was loaned out to French [[Ligue 1]] club [[AS Monaco FC|Monaco]] on a two-season loan, with Bayern Munich having the option to cut the loan short after one season.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.asmonaco.com/en/alexander-nubel-joins-as-monaco/|title=Alexander Nübel joins AS Monaco|website=AS Monaco FC|date=27 June 2021|access-date=28 June 2021}}</ref>

====Since 2023: Loan to VfB Stuttgart with extension for two more years====
On 25 July 2023, Nübel returned to the Bundesliga and joined [[VfB Stuttgart]] on a season-long loan.<ref>{{cite web|website=VfB Stuttgart|url=https://www.vfb.de/en/vfb/latest/news/professionals/2324/an/|title=Alexander Nübel joins VfB|date=25 July 2023|access-date=25 July 2023}}</ref> On 12 April 2024, he signed a contract extension with Bayern Munich until 2029,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://fcbayern.com/en/news/2024/04/alexander-nubel-signs-contract-extension-at-fc-bayern-until-2029 |title=Alexander Nübel signs contract extension at FC Bayern|website=FC Bayern Munich |date=12 April 2024 }}</ref> and his loan was extended for two more years at Stuttgart.<ref>{{cite web|website=VfB Stuttgart|url=https://www.vfb.de/en/vfb/latest/news/professionals/2324/alexander-nuebel-bleibt-beim-vfb-stuttgart/|title=Nübel to stay with VfB|date=12 April 2024|access-date=12 April 2024}}</ref>

==International career==
Nübel was a youth international footballer for Germany.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://datencenter.dfb.de/profil/263670 |title=Alexander Nübel Personenprofil|publisher=[[German Football Association]]|language=de}}</ref> On 16 May 2024, he was named in the 27-man preliminary squad of [[Germany national football team|Germany]] for the [[UEFA Euro 2024]].<ref>{{cite news |date=16 May 2024 |title=Nagelsmann gibt vorläufigen Kader für Heim-EM bekannt |trans-title=Nagelsmann announces provisional squad for home European Championship |url=https://www.dfb.de/maenner-nationalmannschaft/news-detail/nagelsmann-gibt-vorlaeufigen-kader-fuer-heim-em-bekannt-261479/ |language=de |publisher=[[German Football Association]] |access-date=30 May 2024}}</ref> However, on 7 June, he was excluded from the final squad prior to the tournament.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.sportschau.de/fussball/nationalmannschaft/nagelsmann-streicht-nuebel-aus-em-kader,kader-deutschland-100.html |title=Nagelsmann streicht Nübel aus EM-Kader |publisher=Sportschau |language=de |date=7 June 2024 }}</ref> Later that year, on 11 October, he made his senior debut by starting in a 2–1 away victory against [[Bosnia and Herzegovina national football team|Bosnia and Herzegovina]] in the [[2024–25 UEFA Nations League|UEFA Nations League]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.sportschau.de/fussball/nationalmannschaft/nuebel-vor-debuet-umbauarbeiten-im-angriff,video-dfb-126.html |title=Nübel vor DFB-Debüt, Umbauarbeiten im Angriff |publisher=Sportschau |language=de |date=11 October 2024 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.eurosport.de/fussball/uefa-nations-league/2024-2025/nations-league-deutschland-muht-sich-zum-sieg-gegen-bosnien-doppelpacker-deniz-undav-entscheidend_sto20044616/story.shtml |title=Nations League {{!}} Deutschland müht sich zum Sieg gegen Bosnien: Doppelpacker Deniz Undav entscheidend|website=[[Eurosport]]|publisher=[[TNT Sports International]]|language=de |date=11 October 2024 }}</ref> On 21 May 2026, he was selected in Germany’s 26-man squad for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.dfb.de/news/bundestrainer-nagelsmann-gibt-wm-kader-bekannt|title=Bundestrainer Nagelsmann gibt WM-Kader bekannt|publisher=[[German Football Association]]|language=de|date=21 May 2026|access-date=21 May 2026}}</ref>

